"{\"uid\": \"ew.com-full-house-jodie-sweetin-candace-cameron-bure-olympics-comments-8685700\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"\\\"Tell me you do not know about art or history without TELLING me you do not know about art or history,\\\" Sweetin said in an Instagram post.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 138, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 123, \"end\": 132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.278794381795099e-28, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Tanner sisters are fighting again.\", \"from\": 140, \"to\": 178, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On Monday,Jodie Sweetinshared two different posts inher Instagram stories, seemingly making a dig at her TV sister,Candace Cameron Bure, in response to Bure's take on a moment from the2024 Paris Olympicsopening ceremony.\", \"from\": 180, \"to\": 400, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 236, \"end\": 245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.278794381795099e-28, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}, {\"begin\": 295, \"end\": 315, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Candace_Cameron_Bure\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Candace Cameron Bure\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Candace_Cameron_Bure\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Candace_Cameron_Bure\"}, {\"begin\": 311, \"end\": 315, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Bure\", \"score\": 0.9902910458220053, \"rank\": 0.009804142127991165, \"text\": \"Bure\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Bure\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Bure\"}, {\"begin\": 332, \"end\": 336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Bure\", \"score\": 0.9902910458220053, \"rank\": 0.009804142127991165, \"text\": \"Bure\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Bure\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Bure\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During Friday's ceremony, some conservative viewers, including Bure,took issue with what they perceived to be a group of drag queensrecreating Leonardo da Vinci's interpretation ofThe Last Supper.However, the moment was actually meant to depict the feast of Dionysus, a celebratory moment meant to pay tribute to the Greek gods of Mt.\", \"from\": 402, \"to\": 736, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 465, \"end\": 469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Bure\", \"score\": 0.9902910458220053, \"rank\": 0.009804142127991165, \"text\": \"Bure\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Bure\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Bure\"}, {\"begin\": 660, \"end\": 668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.080654691607016e-21, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 719, \"end\": 729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.952117455745851, \"rank\": 0.05029058543687371, \"text\": \"Greek gods\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympus, the namesake of the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 737, \"to\": 780, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Tell me you do not know about art or history without TELLING me you do not know about art or history,\\\" Sweetin wrote alongside a reel mocking those who misunderstood the moment and used it to perpetuate hate against drag queens.\", \"from\": 782, \"to\": 1011, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Michael Tullberg/Getty; Danielle Del Valle/Getty  Bure was one of a handful of celebrities to complain about the moment, despite it never having been intended to represent the religious art work.\", \"from\": 1013, \"to\": 1208, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1030, \"end\": 1035, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"score\": 0.9957461424641542, \"rank\": 0.0035817746186295276, \"text\": \"Getty\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\"}, {\"begin\": 1037, \"end\": 1045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danielle_Jonas\", \"score\": 0.948749569307193, \"rank\": 0.054015141936055035, \"text\": \"Danielle\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danielle_Jonas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danielle_Jonas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was pretty clear, [it was] Dionysus who arrives at the table,\\\" Paris Olympics artistic director Thomas Jolly said in aFrench-language interview.\", \"from\": 1210, \"to\": 1358, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1241, \"end\": 1249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.080654691607016e-21, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 1310, \"end\": 1316, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.7953967552131095, \"rank\": 0.24949665922895303, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Why is he there?\", \"from\": 1359, \"to\": 1376, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Because Dionysus is the Greek god of festivities and wine, and is the father of\\u00a0Sequana, the goddess of the Seine river.\\\"\", \"from\": 1377, \"to\": 1498, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1385, \"end\": 1393, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.080654691607016e-21, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 1401, \"end\": 1406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.9913318686392457, \"rank\": 0.00782236014658473, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}, {\"begin\": 1457, \"end\": 1464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sequana\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sequana\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sequana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sequana\"}, {\"begin\": 1485, \"end\": 1490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999997662599, \"rank\": 2.3346436326184496e-10, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sweetin also shared a post in her Instagram stories breaking down the history of the feast of Dionysus.\", \"from\": 1500, \"to\": 1603, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1534, \"end\": 1543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.278794381795099e-28, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}, {\"begin\": 1594, \"end\": 1602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.080654691607016e-21, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The drag queens of the Olympics were re-creating the feast of Dionysus, not the last supper,\\\" the post explained.\", \"from\": 1604, \"to\": 1718, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1667, \"end\": 1675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.080654691607016e-21, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"And even if you thought it was a Christian reference - what's the harm?\", \"from\": 1719, \"to\": 1791, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1753, \"end\": 1762, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.8964648011691294, \"rank\": 0.11068076346174648, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Why is it a 'parody' and not a tribute?\", \"from\": 1792, \"to\": 1831, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Can drag queens not be Christian too?\\\"\", \"from\": 1832, \"to\": 1870, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Though Sweetin did not call out Bure directly, her post seemed to engage directly with Bure's remarks.\", \"from\": 1872, \"to\": 1974, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1904, \"end\": 1908, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Bure\", \"score\": 0.9902910458220053, \"rank\": 0.009804142127991165, \"text\": \"Bure\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Bure\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Bure\"}, {\"begin\": 1959, \"end\": 1963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Bure\", \"score\": 0.9902910458220053, \"rank\": 0.009804142127991165, \"text\": \"Bure\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Bure\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Bure\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"To watch such an incredible and wonderful event that's gonna take place over the next two weeks and see the opening ceremonies completely blaspheme and mock the Christian faith with their interpretation of the Last Supper was disgusting,\\\" Bure saidin an Instagram video.\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 2246, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2137, \"end\": 2146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.8964648011691294, \"rank\": 0.11068076346174648, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 2230, \"end\": 2239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.278794381795099e-28, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sign up forEntertainment Weekly's\\u00a0free daily newsletterto get breaking TV news, exclusive first looks, recaps, reviews, interviews with your favorite stars, and more.\", \"from\": 2248, \"to\": 2414, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bure later edited the postwith a follow-up,noting that she wasn't buying the Dionysus explanation and that even if she did, it was still inappropriate in her opinion.\", \"from\": 2416, \"to\": 2582, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2493, \"end\": 2501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.080654691607016e-21, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Since posting, many have tried to correct me saying it wasn't about an interpretation of DaVinci's The Last Supper, but a Greek god and the festival of Dionysus; who is a god of lust, insanity, religious ecstasy, ritual madness etc\\\" Bure wrote, doubling down.\", \"from\": 2583, \"to\": 2843, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2673, \"end\": 2680, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.379048059275688e-24, \"text\": \"DaVinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 2683, \"end\": 2698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Last_Supper\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.778613595964608e-27, \"text\": \"The Last Supper\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Last_Supper\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Last_Supper\"}, {\"begin\": 2706, \"end\": 2711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.9913318686392457, \"rank\": 0.00782236014658473, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}, {\"begin\": 2736, \"end\": 2744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.080654691607016e-21, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I st